The semi-finals and final of Euro 2020, which has been delayed by a year due to the pandemic, are scheduled to take place at Wembley on July 6, 7 and 11. 

Wimbledon, which was abandoned in 2020 for the first time since World War II, is due to start on June 28 and golf's British Open runs from July 15 to 18 at Royal St George's in Kent. 

"As we continue to plan for The Championships in 2021, we welcome @10DowningStreet's announcements," said a statement on Wimbledon's official Twitter feed. 

"We look forward to continuing to work with them, @CommonsDCMS (Digital, Culture, Media and Sport) and the rest of sport with the ambition of welcoming spectators safely to our events this summer." 

